-- Mexico Stocks: Cemex, Urbi Desarrollos, Grupo Mexico Decline
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-03-06T21:25:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-06/mexico-stocks-cemex-urbi-desarrollos-grupo-mexico-decline.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3 p.m. Mexico City time.  The IPC  index  fell 1.7 percent to 37,487.63, the biggest
drop since Jan. 13.  Homebuilders and construction-related companies led
declines as the shrinking European economy spurred an exit from
riskier assets.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, dropped 4.3 percent to 9.77 pesos.  Urbi Desarrollos
Urbanos (URBI*)  SAB, Mexico’s third-largest homebuilder by
sales, slid 4.3 percent to 14.10 pesos.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB MM), the country’s largest
mining company, declined 2.5 percent to 38.77 pesos. Copper
declined for a third day in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
